"use strict";(self.webpackChunkworking_group_two_website=self.webpackChunkworking_group_two_website||[]).push([[7567],{96303:function(e){e.exports=JSON.parse('{"title":"Delivery Manager","subtitle":"Permanent employee, full-time - Stockholm","id":"610470","jobDescriptions":["\\n                            <name>The team and your role </name>\\n                            <value>\\n\\n                                <p>Our vision is to create programmable mobile networks to allow our customers and their end-users to create more valuable and useful products and services. We do this by deploying a programmable core network, making it accessible through developer-friendly APIs, and then creating a marketplace where customers and developers can meet. On the journey there we create a consistent, cloud-based, highly efficient core network delivered as-a-service. We know where we\u2019re going, and with a lot of trust in each other, we\u2019ll pave the way there together.\\n</p><p><strong>We are in an exciting expansion phase and in addition to scaling up all our engineering teams we have started to build up a world-class Customer Success team.</strong></p><p>So, if you have a passion for customers and tech, this is a great opportunity to join a strong international team. We are looking for a Delivery Manager (or several actually) with excellent communication and interpersonal skills, who know how to build positive and productive working relationships with customers for business growth. You will work in a dedicated Customer Success Team consisting of Project Managers, Program Managers, and Technical Support Engineers.\\n</p><p><strong>As our Delivery Manager you will:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Drive the delivery of customer integration projects as well as internal roadmap delivery projects that require cross team coordination</p></li><li><p>Ensure projects are delivered in time and with quality</p></li><li><p>Act as a bridge between the customer and internal agile development teams</p></li><li><p>Manage external and internal stakeholder, maintaining communication and aligning expectations</p></li><li><p>Be the face of the project internally and to our customers</p></li><li><p>Prioritization of project backlogs</p></li></ul><br><p><strong>We believe you have:</strong></p><ul><li>A solid background with customer facing delivery projects<br><br></li><li><p>Experience from integration projects, ideally from Telco industry</p></li><li><p>Experience in managing agile development in waterfall delivery projects</p></li><li><p>Experience in mapping HLD documentation to functional requirements for delivery teams</p></li><li><p>Experience with reporting related to project governance&nbsp;</p></li></ul>Terms like IPSec, Sigtran, SS7, Diameter, SIP, BGP, LTE, UMTS, GSM, EPC, IMS should not be foreign to you.<br><br><br>\\n\\n                            </value>\\n                        ","\\n                            <name>Our company culture</name>\\n                            <value>\\n\\n                                <p>What\'s it like to work at Working Group Two?</p><ul><li><p>We are a small team that values getting things done in a professional manner</p></li><li><p>We encourage curiosity and creativity</p></li><li><p>We aim to create a warm and welcoming work environment</p></li><li><p>We treat our coworkers well and offer competitive benefits to employees</p></li><li><p>We work remotely, hybrid and on-site, basically the way each prefer, and have offices in Norway (Oslo and Trondheim) and Sweden, engineering hubs in Germany and Japan, and employees in 11 countries.</p></li><li><p>To learn more about \u201cthe way we roll\u201d we suggest you have a quick read through https://www.wgtwo.com/blog/were-all-grownups-here</p></li></ul>\\n\\n                            </value>\\n                        "]}')}}]);